{{Quote|'Victory Without War.' What's the point of that?|[[Moff/Legends|Moff]] [[Geist (Moff)|Geist]]|<ref name="Legacy (2006) 15">[[Legacy (2006) 15|''Legacy'' (2006) 15]]</ref>}}
'''Victory Without War''' was a campaign launched by [[Galactic Emperor/Legends|Emperor]] [[Jagged Fel]] to peacefully spread the influence of the [[Fel Empire]], providing aid to people and [[Planet/Legends|planets]] ruined by the [[Yuuzhan Vong War]]. One of its programs was the [[Imperial Mission]]. Both [[Fel II|Jagged Fel's son]] and [[Roan Fel|grandson]] continued the program during their reigns, despite opposition from militarist and conservative [[Moff/Legends|Moffs]] like [[Geist (Moff)|Geist]].

The Victory Without War program continued after the [[Sith–Imperial War]] and the rise of [[Darth Krayt's Galactic Empire]], despite the [[One Sith]] in control. After [[Darth Krayt|Krayt's]] death, it was discontinued by Krayt successor, [[Darth Wyyrlok (III)|Darth Wyyrlok]], who favoured the traditional [[Code of the Sith/Legends|Code of the Sith]] instead.

